-- Mauritius Says That Tourist Arrivals Rise 6.8% in First 11 Months of Year
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2010-12-17T08:04:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/mauritius-says-that-tourist-arrivals-rise-6-8-in-first-11-months-of-year.html
Mauritius tourist arrivals increased
6.8 percent to 819,978 people in the first 11 months of 2010
from a year earlier, the Port Louis-based government said in a
statement on its website today.  The number of tourists visiting the Indian Ocean island
rose 9.5 percent to 85,982 in November compared with a year
earlier, the government said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
